{
  "stem": "27748.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I don't remember sort of playing interactions with other schoolmates, although much later-- I'm going to jump ahead for a second.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I went back for my one visit to Germany in 1974, a man came up to me and said, don't you remember me?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were the smallest ones in class and we always sat together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I didn't remember him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't tell him, but I did not remember him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he claims we sat together and had some kind of a friendship, although my memory of all the interactions with the German children were of terror.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the overwhelming feeling I have about the school situation was fear, fear of being alive, fear of being beaten up, fear for my life, all the time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my father read newspapers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was 11 when I left eventually.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father read newspapers, so I suspect he was quite in touch with what was going on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we did not sort of sit down and have discussions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think there were all a series of sort of gut reactions to immediate things that were happening, such as having our windows smashed early.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we did not have strategy sessions.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I know during that time my parents made desperate efforts to get out, for our whole family to get out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We applied to relatives in the United States.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we couldn't get anybody to sponsor us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So a good deal of the atmosphere in the '30s for us was the attempt to get out and not being able to, of our parents making effort.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we did not have sort of strategy sessions of how to cope with life in the community, or how I would cope with the school situation.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
